<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Two potential violations: 1) strlen(realm) is called without any guarantee in this fragment that 'realm' points to a NUL-terminated character array. If a caller supplies a non-terminated buffer (or an invalid pointer), strlen can read past the end of the object and thus violate Rule 21.17. 2) memcpy(nonce, nonce2, NONCE_STD_LEN(digest_size)) copies a number of bytes derived from digest_size into the destination 'nonce' but the function signature provides no size for 'nonce'. If the caller supplies a buffer smaller than NONCE_STD_LEN(digest_size), memcpy will write beyond the bounds of 'nonce' and violate Rule 21.17.
</scenario>

